wiki.content: On “No Regrets,” Eminem teams up with rising star Don Toliver, on a smooth, melodic track. On the track, Em revisits his troubled past and difficult come-up, while also coming to the realization that “he wouldn’t change ” if he could go back and do everything over again, while Don delivers the track’s emotional chorus, which serves as an introspective look into their own origins and the way they impact their loved ones. Em also addresses some of his more recent and prevalent beefs over the past few years, calling out rappers such as Nick Cannon, Machine Gun Kelly and Tyler, The Creator. Don addresses his sadness in being alone, but still is trying very hard not to have any regrets. The song’s production is handled by D.A. Doman, whose hard-hitting instrumental highlights Em’s transition to a more modern trap style. This marks Doman’s third production credit on Music to Be Murdered By, following “Those Kinda Nights” and “Godzilla.” Read more on Last.fm.
